    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "here's the text for section 4.2: \"4.2 Price Adjustments: SwiftRoute shall be entitled to fixed rate pricing throughout the standard fiscal period. However, during designated peak months (defined in Appendix B), the Supplier reserves the right to apply a premium adjustment of up to 5% to the base rate to account for market volatility. Such adjustments shall be applied to all invoices generated during the peak period without the requirement of a secondary written amendment.\"\n\nso what's the verdict? is there any risk of them just raising the rates on us unexpectedly?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
